description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be responsible for assisting in the delivery of the outsourced payroll service to the Trust, in conjunction with the currently appointed external payroll provider.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be working within an internal administrative function associated with the delivery of the payroll service and have knowledge of Agenda for Change (AfC) and Medical &amp; Dental pay regulations and to ensure all contractual changes are interpreted and applied correctly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It would be advantageous if the postholder holds a detailed knowledge of the NHS computerised payroll system (ESR)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To process starters, leavers and changes to pay as notified by an appropriate authorized signatory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Initiate Inter Authority Transfers for new starters as and when required and ensure that the data received is correctly interpreted to update payroll records.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be based at Britannia Park, Southend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMarlon EdwardsJob titleGroup Head of Workforce Systems and InformationEmail addressmarlon.edwards@btuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
